I want you to be maid of honor.

248
00:14:57.570 --> 00:15:00.820
- How do you feel about that?
- The same way you feel about Botox:

249
00:15:00.990 --> 00:15:02.740
Painful and unnecessary.

250
00:15:03.240 --> 00:15:07.990
- Seventy-four, 75, 76. Seventy-six guests.
- Seventy-five sounds better.

251
00:15:08.160 --> 00:15:11.660
A small wedding of 75 guests.

252
00:15:11.830 --> 00:15:14.920
Seventy-six trombones, yes.
Seventy-six guests, no.

253
00:15:15.090 --> 00:15:17.090
As a wedding gift,
Charlotte had given me...

254
00:15:17.250 --> 00:15:19.880
...Anthony Marantino,
friend and wedding planner.

255
00:15:20.050 --> 00:15:21.670
All right.

256
00:15:22.180 --> 00:15:24.010
Well, that's...

257
00:15:24.470 --> 00:15:27.180
Cutthroat. I love it.
I hope you're this decisive...

258
00:15:27.350 --> 00:15:30.270
...when it comes to location and the dress.
- I found the dress.

259
00:15:30.430 --> 00:15:32.850
- What? When?
- Yeah, the other day. I have it.

260
00:15:35.060 --> 00:15:38.530
- This is gonna be good.
- I am so excited.

261
00:15:38.690 --> 00:15:40.530
Okay.

262
00:15:41.030 --> 00:15:42.900
Here it is.

263
00:15:47.450 --> 00:15:49.700
That was the exact reaction
I was aiming for.

264
00:15:50.040 --> 00:15:53.370
It's pretty, but it's... It's so simple.

265
00:15:53.540 --> 00:15:55.420
It's simple and classic.

266
00:15:55.580 --> 00:16:00.710
When I saw it, I thought'
"That is what I should marry Big in."

267
00:16:00.880 --> 00:16:05.180
- Well, who's it by? What's the label?
- No one. I found it at a vintage shop.

268
00:16:06.260 --> 00:16:08.890
The bride wore a dress by no one.

269
00:16:09.060 --> 00:16:11.640
Oh, come on,
you know I'm gonna merchandise it up...

270
00:16:11.810 --> 00:16:14.230
...style it up with some shoes.
Right.

271
00:16:15.440 --> 00:16:17.400
The invitation is fancier than the dress.

272
00:16:17.570 --> 00:16:19.520
- I heard that.
- I meant you to.

273
00:16:20.070 --> 00:16:22.110
Don't tell anyone.

274
00:16:31.410 --> 00:16:35.170
"The ultimate single gal, Carrie
Bradshaw, will be married in Manolos...

275
00:16:35.330 --> 00:16:39.920
...to New York financier
John James Preston come fall."

276
00:16:40.090 --> 00:16:43.260
- Our wedding's on Page Six.
- Who would put that in there?

277
00:16:43.420 --> 00:16:48.720
"Proving to single gals everywhere
that there can be a happy ending over 40."

278
00:16:51.140 --> 00:16:52.640
- Carrie.
- Congratulations.

279
00:16:52.810 --> 00:16:56.310
It seemed everywhere I went,
people had seen Page Six.

280
00:16:56.480 --> 00:17:00.440
Even people you didn't expect,
like my Vogue editor, Enid.

281
00:17:00.610 --> 00:17:03.190
We're putting together
our annual age issue...

282
00:17:03.360 --> 00:17:04.860
...and we'd like you to do 40.

283
00:17:05.030 --> 00:17:07.280
- Great. Who am I interviewing?
- No.

284
00:17:07.450 --> 00:17:09.570
You. You are 40.

285
00:17:09.740 --> 00:17:13.450
I want you to be featured in the magazine
as the 40-year-old...

286
00:17:13.620 --> 00:17:16.290
And here's the brilliant twist.
- Bride.

287
00:17:18.290 --> 00:17:21.590
Wait, I'm... I would be in the magazine?

288
00:17:21.750 --> 00:17:25.220
In bridal couture.
It's a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity...

289
00:17:25.380 --> 00:17:30.510
...so spare me a week of
faux soul-searching and just say yes.

290
00:17:30.680 --> 00:17:34.100
Enid, I am so very flattered,
but honestly, l...

291
00:17:34.270 --> 00:17:35.980
Carrie, Vogue designers.

292
00:17:36.140 --> 00:17:37.810
Vogue photographers.

293
00:17:37.980 --> 00:17:39.650
Vogue airbrushing.

294
00:17:40.270 --> 00:17:43.150
Nod your head. Yes.

295
00:17:46.150 --> 00:17:48.320
Thank you. It will be a sensation.

296
00:17:48.490 --> 00:17:50.950
We're calling it "The Last Single Girl."

297
00:17:51.120 --> 00:17:55.160
Well, I'm hardly the last single girl.

298
00:17:55.330 --> 00:17:59.500
No, but 40 is the last age a woman
can be photographed in a wedding gown...

299
00:17:59.670 --> 00:18:02.590
...without the unintended
Diane Arbus subtext.

300
00:18:02.750 --> 00:18:06.260
I thought the issue was
"Great Style at Every Age."

301
00:18:06.420 --> 00:18:09.510
Style, yes. Bride, no.

302
00:18:14.350 --> 00:18:16.520
- Is that better?
- Just your typical Wednesday.

303
00:18:16.680 --> 00:18:19.190
Hanging out with old friends
like Stanford Blatch...

304
00:18:19.810 --> 00:18:22.690
...and new friends like Vera Wang.

305
00:18:22.860 --> 00:18:26.480
She's looking at home for someone
who didn't think she had the bride gene.

306
00:18:26.650 --> 00:18:29.360
- Well, I guess with the right man...
- And the right dress.

307
00:18:29.910 --> 00:18:33.370
When I get married, I'm wearing
something like that, only bigger.

308
00:18:34.660 --> 00:18:36.160
Beauty. Hot.

309
00:18:36.700 --> 00:18:38.200
Love the veil.

310
00:18:38.370 --> 00:18:40.710
And Carolina Herrera.

311
00:18:43.340 --> 00:18:45.710
Nothing fancy, but it's beautiful.
Good work.

312
00:18:45.880 --> 00:18:47.010
Great, let's do it.

313
00:18:58.230 --> 00:19:00.390
And Christian Lacroix.

314
00:19:09.900 --> 00:19:11.200
And Lanvin.

315
00:19:16.160 --> 00:19:17.200
And Dior.

316
00:19:25.920 --> 00:19:28.500
And Oscar de la Renta.

317
00:19:32.430 --> 00:19:36.720
And finally, Vivienne Westwood.

318
00:19:36.890 --> 00:19:39.220
A dress so special...

319
00:19:39.390 --> 00:19:44.400
...it could bring a wedding tear from
even the most unbelieving of women.

320
00:19:50.530 --> 00:19:54.780
And then, the impossible happened.

321
00:20:21.060 --> 00:20:22.430
And just like that...

322
00:20:22.600 --> 00:20:26.650
...Vivienne Westwood
kicked my sweet little suit's ass.

323
00:20:35.740 --> 00:20:37.450
Can I lean?

324
00:20:44.500 --> 00:20:47.630
Are you the last person in New York
still taking out library books?

325
00:20:47.790 --> 00:20:50.090
I love the smell.

326
00:20:51.340 --> 00:20:52.760
Mm.

327
00:20:54.010 --> 00:20:56.970
Oh. That's an oldie.

328
00:20:57.430 --> 00:20:59.850
"Love Letters of Great Men,
Volume One."

329
00:21:00.010 --> 00:21:02.100
- Oh, am I in there?
- No, no.

330
00:21:02.270 --> 00:21:06.390
But some of your classmates are'
like Voltaire, Napoleon.

331
00:21:07.480 --> 00:21:11.650
- Young lady, you need to get glasses.
- No, I don't. I have yours.

332
00:21:11.820 --> 00:21:14.030
Okay, here's Napoleon.

333
00:21:14.490 --> 00:21:18.160
"My dearest Josephine,
I wake consumed with thoughts of you."

334
00:21:18.320 --> 00:21:21.530
Typical short guy.
Gives it all away upfront.

335
00:21:21.870 --> 00:21:24.830
- Why are you reading this?
- It's research for my new book.

336
00:21:25.000 --> 00:21:28.580
- Oh. What's it about?
- Love.

337
00:21:28.750 --> 00:21:30.380
I used to write about finding love.

338
00:21:30.540 --> 00:21:33.960
Now I wanna write about
what happens after you've found it.

339
00:21:34.130 --> 00:21:35.880
Interesting.

340
00:21:36.050 --> 00:21:39.300
- What happens?
- Mm. Stay tuned.

341
00:21:39.970 --> 00:21:42.220
Oh, here, listen. It's Beethoven.

342
00:21:42.390 --> 00:21:44.770
Bring it, Ludwig.

343
00:21:46.390 --> 00:21:49.900
"My thoughts go out to you'
my immortal beloved.

344
00:21:50.060 --> 00:21:53.860
I can live only wholly with you
or not at all."

345
00:21:54.030 --> 00:21:55.360
Good stuff.

346
00:21:55.530 --> 00:21:57.900
"Be calm my life, my all.

347
00:21:58.070 --> 00:22:00.910
Only by calm consideration
of our existence...

348
00:22:01.080 --> 00:22:03.870
...can we achieve
our purpose to live together.

349
00:22:04.040 --> 00:22:06.450
Oh, continue to love me.
Never misjudge...

350
00:22:06.620 --> 00:22:09.580
...the most faithful heart of your beloved.

351
00:22:09.750 --> 00:22:14.880
Ever thine. Ever mine. Ever ours."

352
00:22:18.800 --> 00:22:21.220
Have you ever written me a love letter?

353
00:22:21.390 --> 00:22:22.850
Does a love fax count?

354
00:22:23.760 --> 00:22:27.890
- When have I ever gotten a love fax?
- Oh, I'm sure my secretary sent you one...

355
00:22:28.060 --> 00:22:30.400
...at some point.
- Yeah.

356
00:22:30.860 --> 00:22:33.940
What can I tell you, baby?
It's not my style.

357
00:22:34.110 --> 00:22:37.490
Besides, those guys had to write.
They were separated from their loves...

358
00:22:37.650 --> 00:22:41.320
...by wars
and hundreds and hundreds of miles.

359
00:22:41.490 --> 00:22:43.620
I'm right here.

360
00:22:43.780 --> 00:22:45.740
Hello.

361
00:22:47.200 --> 00:22:51.290
- You make me very happy.
- Yeah, yeah. Put it in writing.

362
00:22:52.460 --> 00:22:57.130
With my mind prenuptially preoccupied,
I became delinquent with my library books.

363
00:22:57.300 --> 00:23:01.090
So now the tragic love stories
ofWuthering Heights and Love Story...

364
00:23:01.260 --> 00:23:03.390
...were going to cost me
more than a few tears.

365
00:23:03.550 --> 00:23:05.560
Excuse me, which way is the wedding?

366
00:23:05.810 --> 00:23:07.680
Up the stairs.

367
00:23:18.650 --> 00:23:20.780
It was perfect.

368
00:23:20.950 --> 00:23:23.990
Big and I would be married
in the classic New York landmark...

369
00:23:24.160 --> 00:23:27.910
...that housed all the great love stories.

370
00:23:31.080 --> 00:23:32.870
Where is the waiter with the check?

371
00:23:33.040 --> 00:23:36.670
Jeez, Miranda, relax.
Magda hasn't even finished yet.

372
00:23:36.840 --> 00:23:39.460
I still have a brief to work on
when I get home.

373
00:23:39.630 --> 00:23:43.180
- I have to go to the bathroom.
- I'll take him.

374
00:23:43.340 --> 00:23:44.430
Thank you, Magda.

375
00:23:45.350 --> 00:23:49.140
We're gonna wash that beautiful face.
Come, darling.

376
00:23:51.520 --> 00:23:52.520
What?

377
00:23:52.690 --> 00:23:55.190
We can't let the hard-working nanny
finish her supper?

378
00:23:55.360 --> 00:23:58.980
I'm sorry, I'm exhausted.
Brady woke me up at 5 a.m.

379
00:23:59.150 --> 00:24:02.200
- Hey, he woke me up too.
- Yeah.

380
00:24:02.360 --> 00:24:05.160
We gotta stop letting Brady
come into our bed.

381
00:24:09.540 --> 00:24:11.370
You got milk on your top lip.

382
00:24:13.170 --> 00:24:14.330
What now?

383
00:24:14.500 --> 00:24:17.790
- It's like you're always criticizing me.
- I am not.

384
00:24:18.710 --> 00:24:22.880
You wanna go through life with foam
on your lip and no one ever telling you?

385
00:24:30.520 --> 00:24:32.730
Anything you wanna tell me?

386
00:24:39.820 --> 00:24:42.690
Hm. Is there anything you wanna tell me?

387
00:24:49.330 --> 00:24:53.830
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Wait. Wait. Don't come already.

388
00:24:54.000 --> 00:24:57.580
- Yeah.
- No, wait. Get on top.

389
00:24:57.750 --> 00:25:00.380
Let's just get it over with.

390
00:25:04.590 --> 00:25:08.010
I mean, we gotta get up
in four and a half hours.

391
00:25:09.220 --> 00:25:12.680
We never have sex
and you wanna get it over with?

392
00:25:17.900 --> 00:25:21.770
- Steve, we have sex.
- When was the last time we had sex?

393
00:25:22.740 --> 00:25:24.530
Um...

394
00:25:27.280 --> 00:25:30.120
There was snow on the ground.

395
00:25:36.620 --> 00:25:39.290
- How often do you guys have sex?
- Sex.

396
00:25:39.460 --> 00:25:41.290
- Miranda, please.
What?

397
00:25:41.750 --> 00:25:43.880
She's 3.
She doesn't know what it means.

398
00:25:44.050 --> 00:25:46.050
I'm 41 and I still don't know
what it means.

399
00:25:46.220 --> 00:25:48.470
I know, but she is repeating everything.

400
00:25:48.640 --> 00:25:52.810
If I'd known the girl talk was gonna be on
lockdown, I wouldn't have flown 3000 miles.

401
00:25:52.970 --> 00:25:55.600
No, we can talk.
Let's just not use that word.

402
00:25:56.230 --> 00:25:59.770
Fine. How often do you guys...?

403
00:25:59.940 --> 00:26:01.650
- Color?
Thank you.

404
00:26:01.820 --> 00:26:06.150
Well, I can't color enough.
I could color all day every day.

405
00:26:06.320 --> 00:26:10.410
If I had my way,
I would use every crayon in my box.

406
00:26:10.570 --> 00:26:13.830
We get it. You love to color.

407
00:26:13.990 --> 00:26:15.750
Why are you asking?

408
00:26:15.910 --> 00:26:21.130
Well, last night Steve and I were coloring,
and I was just about to...

409
00:26:21.290 --> 00:26:24.050
Come.
I'm sorry, there's no crayon equivalent.

410
00:26:24.210 --> 00:26:27.760
And he wanted to switch positions
and I said:

411
00:26:28.760 --> 00:26:30.340
"Let's just get it over with."

412
00:26:32.930 --> 00:26:35.520
- He kept trying to make it last longer.
- This is bad?

413
00:26:35.680 --> 00:26:38.520
- It is when you have a full-time job.
- I have a full-time job.

414
00:26:38.690 --> 00:26:41.520
You don't also have a 5-year-old,
play dates, PTA meetings...

415
00:26:41.690 --> 00:26:45.150
...and a mother-in-law in a rest home
with advancing Alzheimer's.

416
00:26:45.320 --> 00:26:48.530
We're just going through
a no-coloring phase.

417
00:26:48.700 --> 00:26:51.490
- It comes and goes, right?
Every couple is different.

418
00:26:51.870 --> 00:26:54.370
Harry and I make love
two, three times a week.

419
00:26:54.540 --> 00:26:57.790
- Great, now I feel worse.
- Well, when was the last time for you?

420
00:26:59.790 --> 00:27:01.870
- Six months ago.
- Oh, my.

421
00:27:03.170 --> 00:27:05.170
It sounds long.

422
00:27:05.340 --> 00:27:08.300
- But... But that's a dry spell.
- I bet it is.

423
00:27:08.470 --> 00:27:11.880
Hey, Carrie. What about you and Big?

424
00:27:12.340 --> 00:27:15.390
Come on. I told. Tell.

425
00:27:15.560 --> 00:27:16.760
Mm-mm.

426
00:27:16.930 --> 00:27:18.890
But I will tell you this.

427
00:27:19.060 --> 00:27:20.850
When Big colors...

428
00:27:22.400 --> 00:27:25.820
...he rarely stays inside the lines.

429
00:27:25.980 --> 00:27:28.480
Well, this has been very helpful.

430
00:27:38.250 --> 00:27:40.080
John?

431
00:27:46.920 --> 00:27:49.130
- Hey.
- Come here.

432
00:27:57.310 --> 00:28:00.100
Totally outside the lines.

433
00:28:08.070 --> 00:28:11.440
Well, send it to Smith Jerrod
at the office address.

434
00:28:11.900 --> 00:28:14.240
I gotta go. Something just came up.

435
00:28:16.330 --> 00:28:20.240
- I got a gift for you.
- So far, I like it.

436
00:28:28.710 --> 00:28:30.050
How'd...?

437
00:28:30.630 --> 00:28:33.760
Wait. That was you on the phone
at the auction.

438
00:28:33.930 --> 00:28:38.050
- I knew how much you wanted it.
- But I was gonna buy it for myself.

439
00:28:38.470 --> 00:28:40.310
Well, I wanted to give it to you.

440
00:28:41.140 --> 00:28:43.310
For our anniversary.

441
00:28:43.480 --> 00:28:45.480
We met five years ago today.

442
00:28:46.980 --> 00:28:48.310
Right.

443
00:28:49.400 --> 00:28:50.730
Do you like it?

444
00:28:50.900 --> 00:28:53.820
Well, just to be clear,
this is a ring with diamonds...

445
00:28:53.990 --> 00:28:56.740
...it's not a diamond ring, right?
- Yeah.

446
00:28:57.990 --> 00:29:00.030
Well, in that case, I love it.

447
00:29:00.200 --> 00:29:03.580
It's my second favorite thing
I've ever found in there.

448
00:29:05.330 --> 00:29:10.000
Now, my gift is a little bit more oral.

449
00:29:11.420 --> 00:29:16.340
- Babe, I have to go to bed.
- Bed? It's 7:30.

450
00:29:16.510 --> 00:29:20.180
I have to be at the studio by 6 a.m.
And I need to get a workout in before that.

451
00:29:20.350 --> 00:29:22.010
You see, this is how it starts.

452
00:29:22.180 --> 00:29:26.520
Next thing you know, we're only
having sex three or four times a week.

453
00:29:56.550 --> 00:30:00.510
And that is how Samantha learned
she had a new neighbor.

454
00:30:01.390 --> 00:30:04.310
From then on, night after night...

455
00:30:04.480 --> 00:30:07.060
...while Smith got his beauty sleep...

456
00:30:08.980 --> 00:30:13.730
...Samantha found something
more interesting to watch than TiVo.

457
00:30:17.910 --> 00:30:20.740
- Keep going.
- Okay.

458
00:30:21.780 --> 00:30:23.910
- Keep them closed.
- Okay.

459
00:30:25.410 --> 00:30:28.750
Okay. Open them.

460
00:30:31.080 --> 00:30:33.090
Double doors.

461
00:30:33.250 --> 00:30:35.710
So far, so good.

462
00:30:46.100 --> 00:30:48.230
Oh, my God.

463
00:30:51.480 --> 00:30:56.230
- Oh, you did me proud, mister.
- You like it?

464
00:30:57.610 --> 00:30:58.690
"Like it?"

465
00:31:03.530 --> 00:31:05.700
It's love at first sight.

466
00:31:05.870 --> 00:31:08.080
Oh, my.

467
00:31:08.250 --> 00:31:11.460
Here. Wait.

468
00:31:11.630 --> 00:31:13.170
Hold this.

469
00:31:20.930 --> 00:31:23.800
Now I believe this is all really happening.

470
00:31:24.720 --> 00:31:26.810
I can't believe it sold so fast.

471
00:31:26.970 --> 00:31:29.850
- It's a sign.
- Yeah, it's a sign I priced it too low.

472
00:31:31.270 --> 00:31:34.650
Hey, that's the food. Will you buzz
them in? And money's on the table.

473
00:31:34.820 --> 00:31:38.150
I'm gonna get started on the closet.
I should be done in about 17 years.

474
00:31:38.320 --> 00:31:41.610
All right. Pink Post-it: Take.

475
00:31:41.990 --> 00:31:45.070
Purple: Toss. Yellow: Storage.

476
00:31:45.240 --> 00:31:47.660
Oh, you're very good friends.

477
00:31:53.580 --> 00:31:55.380
Oh, my God.

478
00:31:57.840 --> 00:32:01.170
I can't believe it.
Lily, look who it is. Aunt Samantha.

479
00:32:03.590 --> 00:32:07.180
- What are you doing here?
- A lot of shit went down in this place.

480
00:32:07.350 --> 00:32:09.890
Attention must be paid.

481
00:32:10.480 --> 00:32:11.560
Ah.

482
00:32:13.650 --> 00:32:16.190
Really, champagne.

483
00:32:23.280 --> 00:32:25.200
- Remember this?
- Oh, yeah.

484
00:32:25.370 --> 00:32:28.660
While Samantha put on
The Best of the '80s...

485
00:32:30.080 --> 00:32:33.000
...I put on the worst.

486
00:32:40.170 --> 00:32:41.800
Banana clip.

487
00:32:45.550 --> 00:32:47.350
Yeah.

488
00:32:47.890 --> 00:32:49.560
Work it.

489
00:32:51.770 --> 00:32:53.310
Madonna.

490
00:32:53.480 --> 00:32:56.690
